docs.text: in zoolander , the world's most successful , influential and intellectually-challenged male model derek zoolander wonders , " is there more to life than being really really really good looking ? "
docs.label: positive

docs.text: obviously , the film's creator and star ben stiller asked a similar question when crafting a feature-length movie out of his hilarious vh1/vogue fashion awards short-film subject : can there be more to this film than being really really really silly ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: no , of course not , and it never aspires to be anything more .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: much like derek , zoolander is a sweet simpleton of a movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's not complex in either its social commentary or its comedy , and it never produces any gut-busting laughs ( except maybe a scene when derek's model roommates all die in a tragic " gasoline fight " accident -- a riotously funny take-off of tommy hilfiger ads ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but it has a satisfying handful of strong chuckles , wild characters and performances , and mildly harsh potshots at the fashion industry to keep you amused .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: better yet , this exaggerated version of the original three-minute skit is only blown out to an efficient 95 minutes -- just enough time to string together its goofball plot without exhausting the gag .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: zoolander opens with several fashion bigwigs plotting to assassinate the prime minister of malaysia , since he wants to abolish child labor in his country and thus driving up their costs .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: fashion designer and criminal mastermind jacobim mugatu ( will ferrell ) drafts a plan to brainwash the dumbest fashion model to carry out the evil deed .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: enter derek , whose career is slumping as newcomer hansel ( owen wilson ) takes the spotlight .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on the trail of mugatu's plot is time magazine reporter matilda jeffries ( stiller's real-life wife christine taylor ) , and she's hoping to use mugatu's pawn derek to ultimately foil the scheme .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: much like the austin powers films , zoolander relies heavily on the strength of the talent involved , and this zany comedy features some of the funniest people in entertainment today .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: wilson is hysterical as the young , vain hansel .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ferrell nearly steals the show from everyone as the flamboyant , freakish mugatu in the same way dr . evil upstages everyone in austin powers .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jerry stiller -- ben's dad who's best remembered as frank costanza of seinfeld -- makes a priceless turn as derek's slimy agent maury ballstein .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even ben stiller show alum andy dick shows up as a deranged , large-assed masseuse .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as for ben stiller , it seems his derek has one gag : he's stupid , which plays out in some uproarious one-liners .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: unfortunately , taylor seems out of place and out of her league here .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: maybe it's just because i can't stop seeing her as marcia brady ( who she played in both brady movies ) , making her unbelievable as a dowdy , brainy plain jane who hasn't had sex in two years .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: she leaves me pining for the cynicism of janeane garofolo , who would've added real comic substance to the flimsy role .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: while zoolander is hardly highbrow , its screwball humor is welcome during these trying times , especially considering the gross lack of decent pickings in the theaters these days .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: zoolander's no masterpiece , but a very worthy distraction .
